diff --git a/llvm/docs/P2HubOverlays.rst b/llvm/docs/P2HubOverlays.rst
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..ac1517a1315231547a7b4b328d4bbbaa17e0af6a
--- /dev/null
+++ b/llvm/docs/P2HubOverlays.rst
@@ -0,0 +1,183 @@
+Propeller 2 Hub code overlays
+=============================
+
+Status
+------
+
+This downstream P2 facility is experimental and disabled by default.  It
+solves code *capacity*, not data access: Propeller 2 still executes only from
+its 20-bit Hub address space.  A resident runtime must validate and copy an
+overlay image into the configured Hub slot before entering its body.
+
+Compiler ABI
+------------
+
+Enable the late P2 module transform explicitly::
+
+  clang -target p2-unknown-nuttx \
+    -mllvm -p2-hub-overlays \
+    -mllvm -p2-hub-overlay-slot-address=0x6c000 ...
+
+Select individual functions and their nonzero runtime group in C::
+
+  __attribute__((p2_hub_overlay(1))) int PyExample(void);
+
+Alternatively, ``-mllvm -p2-hub-overlays-all`` selects every safe definition
+in the translation unit.  It requires a nonzero fallback
+``-mllvm -p2-hub-overlay-group=N``.  A large multi-translation-unit program
+such as CPython can instead use ``-mllvm -p2-hub-overlay-auto-groups=N``.
+That mode deterministically hashes the source basename and IR function name
+into contiguous IDs ``1..N``, so independent compiler processes agree without
+a shared mutable counter.  The link-time size assertions are the authoritative
+capacity check; increase or tune ``N`` if a group exceeds the slot.
+
+For exact machine-code-size packing across translation units, use
+link-assigned grouping::
+
+  clang ... \
+    -mllvm -p2-hub-overlays-all \
+    -mllvm -p2-hub-overlay-link-assigned \
+    -mllvm -p2-hub-overlay-source-root=/absolute/source/root \
+    -mllvm -p2-hub-overlay-source-namespace=cpython \
+    -mllvm -p2-hub-overlay-source-variant=3.13-nuttx-p2
+
+The absolute source root and namespace are mandatory.  The variant is
+optional, but builds should pass an explicit stable value when the same
+logical path can have multiple generated or configured implementations.
+Namespace and nonempty variant values must match
+``[a-z0-9][a-z0-9._-]{0,63}``.
+
+The compiler lexically removes ``.`` and ``..`` components, requires the
+module's source filename to remain component-contained beneath the root, and
+hashes only its slash-separated root-relative path.  It does not consult the
+current directory, filesystem, or symlinks.  Consequently identical logical
+sources in different checkout directories have identical identities, while
+different namespaces or variants remain distinct.  Empty, stdin-like, and
+outside-root source filenames fail closed.
+
+Link-assigned sections use domain-separated full lowercase SHA-256 tokens::
+
+  .p2.overlay.auto.<64-hex-TU>.<8-hex-call-order>.<64-hex-function>
+  __p2_overlay_groupref_<64-hex-TU>_<64-hex-function>
+
+The TU token covers namespace, variant, and canonical source path.  The
+function token covers that TU token and the LLVM function name.  The fixed,
+auto-group, and link-assigned fallback options are mutually exclusive.  Code
+that is needed while the slot is being replaced must use::
+
+  __attribute__((p2_hub_resident)) void loader(void);
+
+The equivalent LLVM IR string attributes are ``"p2-hub-overlay-group"="N"``
+and ``"p2-hub-resident"``.
+
+The pass runs after normal IR optimization.  For every selected definition it:
+
+* retains the original function symbol, linkage, visibility, calling
+  convention, and address as a naked resident stub;
+* emits exactly ``calla #\\__p2_overlay_enter`` in that stub, with no
+  prologue, epilogue, or return instruction;
+* moves the original implementation to fixed
+  ``.p2.overlay.body.GGGGGGGG`` or link-assigned
+  ``.p2.overlay.auto.<TU>.<order>.<function>`` with an internal symbol;
+* initially rewrites every old use, including recursion, aliases, direct
+  calls, and function-pointer initializers, to the resident stub;
+* then retargets direct calls between implementations in the same
+  compiler-known nonzero group to the private body; and
+* emits a parallel eight-byte ``{group, body - slot}`` record in
+  ``.p2.xdata.ro.overlay.entries``.  A link-assigned record carries an
+  undefined group-reference relocation that the helper defines absolutely.
+
+All stubs use the common ``.p2.overlay.stubs`` input section and four-byte
+alignment.  Link scripts must retain input order identically for that section
+and ``.p2.xdata.ro.overlay.entries``.  The NuttX resident dispatcher derives a
+table index from ``(stub_return - __p2_overlay_stubs_start) / 4 - 1``; no
+explicit stub ID is passed and argument registers or variadic stack arguments
+are not modified.  Do not enable ``--icf=all``: folding identical input stub
+sections would destroy this positional ABI.  Ordinary ``--gc-sections`` is
+supported when both metadata sections are wrapped in ``KEEP`` as shown by the
+generated script.
+
+Variadic functions are supported.  The implementation retains the original
+signature and native descending P2 ``va_list``.  A direct call or recursion
+between definitions in one module bypasses the veneer when the compiler knows
+both bodies have the same fixed, default, or hash-assigned group.  The caller
+can execute only while that shared image is loaded, so entering the dispatcher
+again cannot add a safety transition.  Function pointers, aliases, indirect
+calls, resident callers, cross-group calls, calls owned by another translation
+unit, and link-assigned groups still use the public veneers.  Because veneer
+entry can copy memory, synchronize, and invoke a loader callback, the late pass
+removes purity/speculation attributes and IR tail-call markers throughout an
+enabled module.
+
+Linking groups
+--------------
+
+``llvm/utils/p2-overlay-link.py`` scans ELF objects or Unix archives and
+generates a deterministic standalone LLD script::
+
+  python3 llvm/utils/p2-overlay-link.py \
+    --slot-address 0x6c000 --slot-size 0x10000 \
+    --lma-address 0x80000 -o overlays.ld objects-or-archives...
+  ld.lld -T overlays.ld -o image.elf objects-or-archives...
+
+The tool rejects group zero, missing group IDs, malformed objects/archives,
+unaligned slots, old/truncated/uppercase link-assigned token spellings,
+duplicate TU call orders or group references, and slots beyond the pinned
+``0x7c000`` board-loader limit.  It keeps small translation units whole and
+uses the compiler's call-local order when a large TU must be split, then packs
+the resulting units under the exact input-section sizes and alignments.
+It emits one LLD ``OVERLAY`` output section per group.  All groups have the
+same VMA and consecutive distinct LMAs, plus per-group size assertions.  The
+resident image build must use the same slot address passed to the compiler.
+
+The generated ELF contains enough deterministic information for a host packer:
+
+* contiguous four-byte stub symbols and parallel entry records;
+* one named executable output section per runtime group;
+* fixed group VMA, distinct group LMA, decoded size, and start/end/load
+  symbols; and
+* internal body symbols whose values are entry offsets from the shared slot.
+
+A production NuttX linker script normally incorporates the generated
+``OVERLAY`` block rather than using the standalone script.  Group payloads
+must be removed from the ordinary serial-loaded Hub binary and placed in the
+validated PSRAM/container backing image.  CRC and packed-image source offsets
+are container responsibilities, not compiler relocations.
+
+For a NuttX base script that already owns resident ``.text``, data, stubs,
+entries, the writable group table, and slot symbols, request a composable
+second ``SECTIONS`` block::
+
+  p2-overlay-link.py --fragment-only \
+    --slot-address 0x6c000 --slot-size 0x10000 \
+    --lma-address 0x80000 -o overlays-fragment.ld objects-or-archives...
+
+The fragment emits no resident output sections.  It defines the absolute
+``__p2_overlay_group_count`` as the complete runtime table count: one reserved
+group-zero record plus every nonresident group.  It verifies that the base
+script's slot symbols match its address and size, and emits only the executable
+``OVERLAY`` groups, their symbols, and capacity/alignment assertions.
+P2-enabled LLVM builds copy the utility into the build ``bin`` directory and
+install it into the LLVM tools directory; its canonical source remains
+``llvm/utils/p2-overlay-link.py``.
+
+Fail-closed boundaries
+----------------------
+
+An explicitly selected unsupported function is a compiler fatal error.  In
+overlay-all mode it remains resident and the compiler prints its name and a
+summary count.  Current unsupported cases are:
+
+* replaceable/interposable linkage and COMDAT definitions;
+* existing naked, interrupt, COG/LUT, startup, constructor, or destructor
+  functions;
+* ``blockaddress``/computed-label uses and ELF ifunc resolvers;
+* exception unwinding, ABI prefix/prologue data, and ``returns_twice``; and
+* setjmp/longjmp control flow, because the runtime shadow stack is not yet
+  unwind-aware.
+
+The resident dispatcher/loader, process bootstrap, and overlay runtime symbol
+prefixes are always excluded.  Overlay execution is currently a single-slot
+runtime policy; concurrency, cancellation, longjmp, and exception unwinding
+require additional target runtime coordination before those cases can be
+enabled.
